Except it's not a bug, it's an intended behavior. The 'agencies' in giving aircraft a purpose contracts generally only want you taking one contract of theirs at a time.

 

There are some exceptions and ways around it, for example you can take a charter flight, an airline flight, an aerial tour, and a 'take some people flying'  contract at once and complete them all by stuffing all of the requested kerbals into one aircraft. But that's barely worth considering an exception, as the agencies offering those contracts are all different, IIRC.

EDIT: Here are the craft files for a working bouy and 

Working stuff to test with, all vanilla (99% certain).

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

The subassembly can be placed on the underside of a wing or in a downward facing cargo bay. I release them at around 120-175m ASL going between 100-130m/s. 120m altitude is somewhat risky to do until you are used to it, however it deploys them fairly quickly onto the water.

 

The seaplane has notes in the description, I would recommend at least the first upgrade to the SPH for basic action groups so that you can use reverse thrusters and flaps to slow yourself down more easily.
NOTE: for keyboard flight I highly suggest precision controls (caps lock by default) as the craft was designed for joystick flight originally, but you can fly it easily with keyboard as well (reduce the authority limiter if you're having trouble with it.

The seaplane was designed for multiple contracts at once, so has 4 extra seats for passengers.
